        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 6:35PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 635 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Kenton, or 38 miles southwest of Springfield,
moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Baca
and southeastern Las Animas Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
